# .doc-contract — doc-surface tiers (ADR 0005). First match wins.
# Asserted in CI by claude/scripts/check-doc-truth.sh.

# Living — kept current as a side effect of the merge loop
LIVING        README.md
LIVING        CHANGELOG.md
LIVING        ROADMAP.md
LIVING        CLAUDE-GUIDE.md
LIVING        docs/BRANCH_PROTECTION.md
LIVING        docs/WINDOWS.md
LIVING        claude/scripts/README.md
LIVING        claude/chrome/WSL-CHROME-FOR-BORIS.md
LIVING        codex/README.md
LIVING        .github/CONTRIBUTING.md
LIVING        .github/SECURITY.md

# Source — markdown-as-config: rules, skills, agents, templates
SOURCE        claude/CLAUDE.md
SOURCE        claude/AgentPack.md
SOURCE        claude/agents/*.md
SOURCE        claude/skills/*/SKILL.md
SOURCE        codex/AGENTS.md
SOURCE        codex/skills/*/SKILL.md
SOURCE        .github/ISSUE_TEMPLATE/*.md
SOURCE        .github/PULL_REQUEST_TEMPLATE.md

# Historical — point-in-time records (banner or ADR Status/Date header)
# (Plans/ is gitignored — untracked files are invisible to the checker.)
HISTORICAL    docs/adr/*.md

# Guards. Open work lives in GitHub issues, not active docs.
# (SOURCE exempt: PR-template platform checkboxes, plan-executing skills.)
BANNED:LIVING,GENERATED ^\s*[-*] \[ \]
